data.enText: a deep crack or opening in the ground

data.chText: （两个人或团体之间的）巨大分歧，显著差别
data.enText: a very big difference between two people or groups, for example because they have different attitudes

means: (两个人或团体之间的)巨大分歧，显著差别

tr: a deep opening in the earth's surface

value.def: A chasm is a very deep crack in rock, earth, or ice.
If you say that there is a chasm between two things or between two groups of people, you mean that there is a very large difference between them.

example.ex: ...the chasm that divides the worlds of university and industry.
example.tran: 将大学和企业两个世界分隔开的鸿沟

example.ex: ...the chasm between rich and poor in America.

gramarinfo.label: usu with supp, oft N <l>between</l> pl-n

value.tran: (事物或团体间的)显著差距，巨大分歧
